recipe.label: California Pizza Kitchen's Dakota Smashed Pea & Barley Soup
Thanksgiving Pizza
ingredientLines: 1 lb. fresh prepared pizza dough, at room temperature
6 oz. white Cheddar cheese, shredded (about 1 1/2 cups)
1 1/4 cups cooked, peeled sweet potato, cut into cubes
1 1/2 cups chopped or shredded roast turkey
1 1/2 cups prepared stuffing or dressing, crumbled into large pieces

ingredients.text: 1 lb. fresh prepared pizza dough, at room temperature
6 oz. white Cheddar cheese, shredded (about 1 1/2 cups)
1 1/4 cups cooked, peeled sweet potato, cut into cubes
1 1/2 cups chopped or shredded roast turkey
1 1/2 cups prepared stuffing or dressing, crumbled into large pieces

instructionLines: How to Make It Step 1 Preheat oven to 450°F.
Roll dough out into an 18-inch round, and place on baking sheet lined with parchment paper.
Bake in preheated oven until golden brown, 7 to 9 minutes.
Discard parchment paper.
Step 2 Stir together cranberry sauce and barbecue sauce in a small bowl; spread evenly over crust.
Top evenly with Cheddar and mozzarella.
Step 3 Toss together sweet potatoes, Brussels sprouts, oil, salt, and pepper in a bowl.
Spread sweet potato mixture evenly over cheese.
Top evenly with turkey and crumbled stuffing.
Step 4 Bake at 450°F until cheese is golden and bubbly, 8 to 10 minutes.
Drizzle with warm gravy.

recipe.label: Tuna Pizza
instructionLines: Coat the tortilla in the eel sauce and toast in oven or over grill until crispy. (Be sure to keep sometime over it if it begins to curl.)
Place the ahi tuna slices on top of the tortilla, completely covering.
Add the olives, jalapeno, tomatoes and red onion; slice the pizza into six pieces.
Add a drop of Tabasco sauce on each slice.
Using a squirt bottle, cover the pizza with thin lines of anchovy aioli.
Season with sea salt and garnish with micro cilantro to serve.

recipe.label: Oil-Free, Fat-Free Veggie Pasta Sauce
ingredientLines: 1 jar Roasted Red Peppers packed in water
2 tbsp Mrs. Dash Garlic and Herb Seasoning
1 cup Water (can adjust to make sauce desired thickness)

ingredients.text: 1 jar Roasted Red Peppers packed in water
2 tbsp Mrs. Dash Garlic and Herb Seasoning
1 cup Water (can adjust to make sauce desired thickness)

instructionLines: In a large saucepan combine Carrots, Onion and entire jar of Roasted Red Peppers.
Bring to a simmer and let cook approximately 15 to 20 minutes until carrots are soft.
Remove from heat and puree with immersion blender, food processor or blender.
Return to saucepan and return to a simmer and add Tomato Paste, Basil, Italian Seasoning, Mrs.
Dash, Red Pepper Flakes, Sugar and White Pepper.
Add desired amount of water to create a slightly thick sauce consistency, remember you can add more water later if it is too thick for your taste.
Let simmer for at least one hour, and make sure you cover the pot it will make a mess.
Stir occasionally to make sure it is not sticking and add more water as desired.
Seasoning can be adjusted to your taste as well, I like more garlic and basil, you might not.
Serve hot over pasta or any other dish that calls for a rich tomato sauce.
If using for pizza, remember not to thin too much.
Serving Size: Makes 4 Servings Number of Servings: 4 Recipe submitted by SparkPeople user TAMLETTIERI.

recipe.label: Pizza triangles
instructionLines: Method Step 1 Preheat oven to 180°C/160°C fan-forced.
Combine ham, cheese, olives, oregano and sauce in a bowl.
Place 1 pastry sheet on a flat surface.
Brush with butter.
Top with 1 pastry sheet.
Cut into 3 long strips.
Cover remaining pastry with a damp tea towel so it doesn't dry out.
Step 2 Place 1 tablespoon ham mixture in 1 corner of pastry.
Fold over diagonally to form a triangle.
Continue folding, retaining triangle shape.
Place on tray lined with baking paper.
Repeat with remaining pastry, butter and ham mixture.
Brush with remaining butter.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden and crisp.
Serve.

recipe.label: Cheesy risotto-stuffed capsicums
ingredientLines: 2 x 250g packets arborio rice risotto base
2 cups Massel chicken style liquid stock (see notes)

ingredients.text: 2 x 250g packets arborio rice risotto base
2 cups Massel chicken style liquid stock (see notes)

instructionLines: Method Step 1 Preheat oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced.
Grease a 4.5cm-deep, 21cm x 28cm (top) flameproof baking dish.
Slice tops from capsicums.
Discard tops.
Scoop out seeds and membrane.
Stand in prepared pan (see note).
Bake for 20 minutes or until just tender.
Preheat grill on high.
Step 2 Meanwhile, heat oil in a large frying pan over medium heat.
Cook onion and garlic for 3 to 4 minutes or until softened.
Add eggplant.
Cook for 2 to 3 minutes or until just tender.
Add rice.
Stir to break up lumps.
Add stock.
Bring to a simmer.
Simmer, stirring occasionally, for 8 to 10 minutes or until liquid has absorbed.
Step 3 Stir in basil and half the cheese.
Divide rice mixture between capsicums.
Top with remaining cheese.
Place baking dish under grill for 2 to 3 minutes or until browned.
Serve with salad.

recipe.label: Pizza Pockets
instructionLines: Preheat oven to 325 degrees F.
To make the dough: Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water.
Add olive oil, then the flour and salt.
Mix together with a dough hook (or by hand) at medium speed until well incorporated.
Set aside.
Prepare your fillings: I like to chop up pretty much whatever veggies I have on hand.
Green peppers, mushrooms, olives, or whatever you like on your pizza.
Chop up your meat.
I usually use deli meat, but you could cook up a chicken breast and chop that up too – really, you can use whatever kind of meat you have on hand.
Prepare your pizza sauce.
I tend to just add spices to a can of tomato sauce, but you could also just use a can of pizza sauce.
All of the filling prep should take about 10 minutes, which is exactly how long you need to let the dough sit for.
Take your dough out and knead it 10-15 times.
Divide it into 6 peices.
Take one peice, shape it into a ball, and then roll it out nice and thin (thin enough that you can fit the fillings in, but not so thin that it will just split open.)
Spoon on some pasta sauce, then some meat, peppers, and top with some cheese.
Pick up the dough on two sides and pinch together.
Do the same with the other two sides.
Then take the 4 “open” corners and pinch them up too.
Make sure it’s all pinched together really well so it won’t break open while cooking.
Do the same with the remaining 5 pieces of dough.
Place on cookie sheet (lining it with parchment paper would make for much easier clean up then I had).
Bake at 325 F for approximately 30 minutes.
I kept peeking in at mine every 5 minutes after the initial 15 minutes, just to keep an eye on it.
When the top is golden brown, they are ready! *If you would like to see step-by-step photos of the folding up process, you can click on the related link which takes you to my blog.
